# jemdoc: menu{MENU}{bio.html}

Gongguo Tang is an Associate Professor in the [https://www.colorado.edu/ecee/ Department of
Electrical, Computer & Energy Engineering] at the [https://www.colorado.edu University of Colorado Boulder].
Before that he was an Associate Professor in the [http://electrical.mines.edu/ Department of Electrical Engineering] at
the [http://www.mines.edu Colorado School of Mines]. He was a visiting scholar at the
[http://simons.berkeley.edu Simons Institute for the Theory of Computing] at the University of California, Berkeley
and a postdoc working with [http://nowak.ece.wisc.edu Professor Robert Nowak] at the University of Wisconsin-Madison
and [http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/~brecht/ Professor Benjamin Recht]  at the University of California, Berkeley. He received his PhD in Electrical Engineering from Washington University in St. Louis
under the supervision of [http://www.ese.wustl.edu/~nehorai/ Professor Arye Nehorai], and a Bachelor degree in Mathematics
from [https://www.en.sdu.edu.cn Shandong University], China.
